a(p^2 + mn) = b^2m + c^2n
m = kc
n = kb
k = \frac{a}{b + c}
p^2 = bc\left(1 - \left(\frac{a}{b + c}\right)^2\right)
CY^2 = ab\left(1 - \left(\frac{c}{a + b}\right)^2\right)
BX^2 = ac\left(1 - \left(\frac{b}{a + c}\right)^2\right)
